    1. Dizziness & Lightheadedness [ - ]
    2. Sexual Dysfunction [ not checked ] 
    3. Urination Changes - includes frequent urination and possible nighttime bathroom visits
    4. Fatigue & Weakness - Persistent tiredness and lethargy that may affect daily activities
    5. Electrolyte Imbalances - Especially with diuretics; can lead to low potassium levels and muscle problems
    6. Gastrointestinal Issues - Including nausea, constipation, diarrhea, and stomach upset
    7. Drug-Specific Reactions:
        ◦ ACE inhibitors: dry cough
        ◦ Calcium channel blockers: ankle swelling
        ◦ Beta-blockers: cold hands/feet
          